channel.title: Project Fnatic- A different old school project
channel.description:
[IMG]http://i429.photobucket.com/albums/qq20/nathanz1_2008/pfn_zpse861a361.png[/img]
[B]Hello and welcome to my thread! My name is nathan and i am going to be working on a project. I'm not sure what the project will consist of as i am looking for ideas but i have a general view of what i am going to do. [size=18pt]This is NOT a remake[/size] although it is at the moment i am going to change it to make it more fun for the players to make it unique and have all the current details but without the low exp rates, without the waiting to pk and fight monsters. I want to make something like nothing that has been made before. [/B]
Now what i plan to do is generate a professional team with every aspect of the game including the website. If you think you're good enough to apply then fill out the application on the website ( Which was quickly put together i will work more on it when i have time ) and i will reply as soon as i see it. There is many roles to be filled.
I have been working with RSPS since 2006 and started java programming early 2007. I would love for this project to go far. Ok here's some pictures for you to get a taster. The pictures are from my server "project fnatic remake" which is the same source which i'm using for this. It's a perfect base to be creative with. Clue scroll system:
[youtube]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2BgFUOCVXaE&feature=youtu.be[/youtube]

item.description:
@enzo42 wrote:

nathanz:

If that’s what you think buddy. I’ve took 2006scape, actually got it to work. re-done ground items, redone logins, redone most of the horrible methods they had. Maybe you shouldn’t judge a book by it’s cover. This is not a remake if you have read the introduction. I am planning on doing something different with the source i had released about a month ago which is where the pictures is from, thanks for your constructive criticism though.

I see it as leeching when you show off content that others made without even mentioning the original creators.

Good Luck though
